In calculating the value of the distributive shares the following deductions and no others shall be allowed:
Debts of the decedent, except debts secured by property not subject to the tax jurisdiction of Kentucky; and except debts barred by the statute of limitations;
Taxes accrued and unpaid, except those on property not subject to the tax jurisdiction of Kentucky;
Death duties paid to foreign countries;
Federal estate taxes, in the proportion which the net estate in Kentucky subject to federal estate taxes bears to the total net estate everywhere subject to federal estate taxes; all calculations are subject to approval by the Department of Revenue;
Drainage, street, or other special assessments due and unpaid which are a lien on said property;
Funeral, monument, and cemetery lot maintenance expenses actually paid not exceeding in total five thousand dollars ($5,000);
Commission of executors and administrators in the amount actually allowed and paid;
Cost of administration, including attorney's fees actually allowed and paid.
